{#
  Triton COMMANDMENT.md template.

  Replaces run/preprocess/commandment.py for the Triton (harness-path)
  case. Consumed by ExplorePhase; output must still pass
  kernel_languages.contract.validate_commandment().

  Jinja vars (per plan §13.2-E):
    - kernel_path         : absolute path to kernel.py
    - harness_path        : absolute path to harness.py
    - repo_root           : absolute path to repo root (for PYTHONPATH)
    - inner_kernel        : bool (True -> inner-kernel setup block)
    - profile_replays     : int (profiler replay count; default 3)

  For the eval-command (HIP) path, a separate commandment.j2 lives
  under kernel_languages/hip/ with different SETUP / CORRECTNESS /
  BENCHMARK / FULL_BENCHMARK / PROFILE bodies. Downstream
  _validate_and_fix still runs on the rendered output to catch any
  regressions.
#}
# Commandment

Evaluation contract for this kernel. All five sections below are
mandatory and enforced by kernel_languages/contract.py::validate_commandment.

## Setup

```bash
export GEAK_WORK_DIR="${GEAK_WORK_DIR:-{{ repo_root }}}"
# Keep the Triton/JIT compile cache OUTSIDE the worktree so the per-round patch
# capture never sweeps compiled blobs (*.hsaco / IR) into the diff (which broke
# re-apply and pinned GEAK's A/B speedup at 1.0x). Honour an inherited value
# (GEAK sets GEAK_JIT_CACHE_DIR/TRITON_CACHE_DIR in the eval env); only the
# default lands in /tmp, keyed per GPU slot.
printf '#!/bin/bash\nexport PYTHONPATH=%s:%s:${PYTHONPATH}\nexport HIP_VISIBLE_DEVICES=%s\nexport GEAK_JIT_CACHE_DIR="${GEAK_JIT_CACHE_DIR:-/tmp/geak_jit_cache/gpu${GEAK_GPU_DEVICE:-0}}"\nexport TRITON_CACHE_DIR="${TRITON_CACHE_DIR:-${GEAK_JIT_CACHE_DIR}/triton}"\ncd "%s" && exec python3 "$@"\n' "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}" "${GEAK_REPO_ROOT:-{{ repo_root }}}" "${GEAK_GPU_DEVICE:-0}" "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}" > ${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh && chmod +x ${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh
{% if inner_kernel -%}
mkdir -p "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/_work"
cp "{{ kernel_path }}" "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/_work/kernel.py"
touch "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/_work/__init__.py"
{%- endif %}
```

## Correctness

```bash
${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh {{ harness_path }} --correctness
```

## Benchmark

```bash
${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh {{ harness_path }} --benchmark
```

## Full Benchmark

```bash
${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh {{ harness_path }} --full-benchmark
```

## Profile

```bash
kernel-profile "${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/run.sh {{ harness_path }} --profile" \
  --gpu-devices ${GEAK_GPU_DEVICE:-0} \
  --replays {{ profile_replays | default(3) }} \
  --json -o ${GEAK_WORK_DIR}/profile.json
```
